-- Cosco Shipping Climbs Most in Month on Rights Offering Approval, Upgrade
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-21T01:52:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/cosco-shipping-climbs-most-in-month-on-rights-offering-approval-upgrade.html
COSCO Shipping Co. rose the most in
more than a month in Shanghai trading after its rights offer
plan was approved. The stock’s rating was raised by Shenyin &
Wanguo Securities Co.  The shares jumped 6.7 percent to 8.48 yuan as of 9:37 a.m.
local time, the biggest advance since Nov. 2.  The Chinese shipper said it received approval from the
China Securities Regulatory Commission to sell 393 million
shares through a rights offer, according to an exchange filing.  Shenyin & Wanguo analysts Zhang Xilin and Zhou Meng raised
their recommendation on the stock to “buy” from “outperform,’’
citing the recovery of the multi-purpose vessel market.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
